ELECTION OF 1876
	Republican - Rutherford B. Hayes
	Democrat - Samuel J. Tilden
	Tilden 1 vote short from majority, 20 disputed electorial votes
	after Congress created a tiebreaker, Hayes received the 20 electorial votes
	Rutherford B. Hayes wins
	Compromise of 1877
		Hayes will become president, and withdraw federal troops from the South, put a southerner in his cabinet,
		give financial aid to the south, and support Texas
	Legacy of Reconstruction
		period of time where African Americans have rights and support, KKK, voting rights limited, 4800 lynching

